  "text": "One who sews two stitches is liable. And that is when he tied the ends of the thread this way and that way, so that the stitch holds and does not undo. But if he ties more than two stitches, he is liable even if he does not tie [them], for the stitch is lasting. And one who stretches the thread of a stitch on Shabbat is liable – since it is from the auxiliaries of sewing.",
